WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY return_date DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
)
SELECT
    return_id,
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        p.name AS product_name,
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name,
        oi.item_id,
        oi.quantity AS items_sold,
        r.return_date,
        r.reason,
        r.status
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    SUM(items_sold) AS total_items_sold,
    SUM(CASE WHEN r.return_date IS NOT NULL THEN items_sold ELSE 0 END) AS total_items_returned,
    SUM(items_sold) - SUM(CASE WHEN r.return_date IS NOT NULL THEN items_sold ELSE 0 END) AS total_items_not_returned,
    ROUND(
        SUM(CASE WHEN r.return_date IS NOT NULL THEN items_sold ELSE 0 END) * 100.0 / 
        NULLIF(SUM(items_sold), 0),
        2
    ) AS return_rate_percent
FROM source
GROUP BY category_name
ORDER BY return_rate_percent DESC
